snippet.textDisplay: It's mildly interesting how Hollywood and the brain-dead zombies whom worship them constantly preach about feminism and the strength of women, yet every time they get the opportunity to back up their words they choke and fail at a golden opportunity to immortalize said beliefs on screen. This is a prime example, instead of sticking with the true story line of Birds of Prey and what it represents, they butcher it, instead of having the group founded by a strong-willed young woman whom continued to thwart crime even after she was made a paraplegic by a psychotic sociopath, they instead have the group founded by the loyal Stockholm lapdog of said sociopath. Even more, instead of being crime-fighters, they're lowered to being bodyguards for said lapdog, and that's not even getting into how the movie even portrays said character's backstories, are they the strong women whom grew strong because of hardships they faced or are they just like Harley Quinn? This isn't the first time Hollywood's spit on the comics and more especially their heroines, Wonder Woman, who has gone toe-to-toe with the likes of Darkseid and Doomsday was reduced to being Steve Trevor's fan-girl in the movies, Jean Grey, a woman with the power to annihilate entire galaxies is reduced to a sniveling little girl in the movies, and Mystique, a woman whom had been around for a hundred years and kicked even Wolverine around is reduced to Magneto's personal pet, whom in the comics, she constantly thrashed and under-minded, even taking over his own group, the Brotherhood of Mutants. I actually do like Harley Quinn, but Birds of Prey is something that shouldn't be butchered in such a way, they could have done a movie based on Harley Quinn's actual comic franchise where she leaves Joker to start her own life in Coney Island, a franchise in which she eventually went to war against Joker and the entire DC villain community and proved herself someone to not be trifled with.
